post_text:
As the BCSD starts week two of school, here are a few reminders to parents and students. (1) Please screen your child each morning using the checklist. If your child is ill, please keep them home and notify the school. (2) School building doors do not open until 7:30. Please do not send or drop your child off prior to 7:30. (3) Face coverings are strongly recommended on the bus and also anywhere social distancing of 6 feet is not possible.

Week two will follow the same format as week one. Students whose last name start with "A-J" will attend Monday and Wednesday and students whose last name starts with "K-Z" will attend Tuesday and Thursday.

Looking forward to a great week! As always if you have any questions, please contact your child's school.

post_text: BCSD will start school on Monday, August 17th. Students whose last name start with A-J will attend on Monday and Wednesday and students whose last name starts with K-Z will attend on Tuesdays and Thursdays. Busses will be running and masks are strongly recommended to be worn on the bus and wherever social distancing of 6 feet is not possible. Breakfast and lunch will be served. Breakfast will be available at the AC for PK-5th and at the MS and HS for grades 6-12. Parents, please pre-screen your child before sending them to school. If they have any symptoms on the checklist, please keep them home and call the school. The checklist can be found on our school website--bennettco@k12.sd.us. If you have any questions, please call the school. Thanks

post_text: For Friday evenings Prom Walk we wanted to let you know our plan. We would like to have Juniors, Seniors, Sophomore Severs and their dates line up in their vehicles by the park, between 5:15 and 5:30. Mrs. Smokov and Mr. Buckles will be putting them in the order to walk down Main Street. We are asking all students to stay in their vehicles until time to start the walk. Public will be welcomed to park along Main Street to see the kids. There will be a few places set up for them to stop and take photos. At the end by Mary Kay's building Missy Slattery take official prom photos and the kids will be able to get some snacks. They will then need to return to their vehicles until the walk is over. Please follow the social distancing guidelines. Junior parents please bring your snacks to Mary Kay's to be set up.around 5. If you have any questions please contact Mandi Smokov or Jason Buckles.

post_text:
As a class you have maintained a closeness that many have never, and because of our current circumstances, you will always have that. I miss the excitement in the senior hallways when the countdown gets closer. I miss hearing about the supposable senior prank that never gets pulled off, and how I pretend that I would be mad if something happened. I miss seeing the formation of your legacy with your Senior Bricks, and the conversations I have gotten to have each year while they’re being painted.

I miss many things, but all the memories I have of the great things this class has done, brings a smile to my face. Thank you for being the class you have been, and I am anxious to see all the great things you accomplish.

I miss seeing the formation of your legacy with your Senior Bricks, and the conversations I have gotten to have each year while they’re being painted.

I miss many things, but all the memories I have of the great things this class has done, brings a smile to my face. Thank you for being the class you have been, and I am anxious to see all the great things you accomplish.

post_text:
Let it Shine Campaign
Thursday night April 16th at 8:20(20:20), Bennett County will be participating in the Let it Shine Campaign. The Let it Shine Campaign, is a movement across the Nation for school to turn on their stadium lights to celebrate our medical workers, first responders, teachers and our seniors. We are asking that everyone that can, to please drive by the football field starting at East School Street by Sod's, and to show support by honking your horn. Please comply with social distancing rules and stay in your cars. We hope to see and hear everyone.
